properties.name: Reduit Beach

properties.name: Rodney Bay Marina

properties.name: Cap Estate
properties.description: Upscale residential area with luxury villas, golf course (St. Lucia Golf & Country Club), Sandals Cap Maison.

properties.name: Gros Islet Town
properties.description: Historic fishing village. Famous Friday Night Jump-Up street party. Local shops, restaurants.

properties.name: Pigeon Island National Landmark
properties.description: National park. Fort Rodney, Signal Peak (hiking), Pigeon Island causeway. Historical military site. Entry fee: EC$40.

properties.name: Daren Sammy Cricket Ground
properties.description: International cricket venue (capacity ~15,000). CPL franchise matches, concerts, national events.

properties.name: Bois d'Orange
properties.description: Growing suburban area between Castries and Rodney Bay. Residential developments, schools.

properties.name: Vieux Fort Town
properties.description: Second largest town. Commercial centre, government services, market, banks.

properties.name: Vieux Fort Free Zone
properties.description: Free zone for manufacturing and warehousing. Tax incentives for export-oriented businesses. BPO operations.
properties._source_detail: Government free zone boundaries + satellite imagery

properties.name: Hewanorra International Airport
properties.description: Main international airport (UVF). 9,000ft runway. Serving 9 airlines. US$175M modernization project underway.

properties.name: Sandy Beach / Pointe Sable
properties.description: Windswept beach popular with kitesurfers and windsurfers. Sandy Beach bar.

properties.name: Soufriere Town
properties.description: Original French capital. Historic waterfront town. Local shops, restaurants, diving operators.

properties.name: Pitons Management Area (UNESCO)
properties.description: UNESCO World Heritage Site since 2004. Gros Piton (770m) and Petit Piton (743m). Marine/terrestrial protected area. Geothermal resources.

properties.name: Sugar Beach / Jalousie
properties.description: Viceroy Sugar Beach (Beachcomber). Ultra-luxury resort between the Pitons. One of the Caribbean's most iconic settings.

properties.name: Sulphur Springs
properties.description: World's only drive-in volcano. Sulphur springs, mud baths, botanical gardens. Major tourist attraction. Entry: EC$18.

properties.name: Diamond Falls / Soufriere Estate
properties.description: Diamond Falls waterfall, mineral baths, botanical gardens. Historic Soufriere Estate. Entry: EC$20.

properties.name: Fond Doux Estate
properties.description: Working 135-acre cocoa estate and boutique hotel. Heritage cocoa processing, Creole cottages.

properties.name: Marigot Bay
properties.description: Stunning protected harbour. Capella Marigot Bay Resort & Marina. Hurricane hole. Yacht services. Film location (Doctor Dolittle).

properties.name: Anse la Raye
properties.description: Fishing village. Famous Friday Night Fish Fry. Authentic Creole dining. Anse Cochon Beach nearby.

properties.name: Canaries
properties.description: Smallest district. Quiet fishing village between Anse la Raye and Soufriere.
properties._source_detail: Manually mapped from satellite imagery and local knowledge

properties.name: Dennery Village
properties.description: Atlantic coast fishing town. Dennery Fish Fiesta. Agriculture (bananas, root crops).

properties.name: Micoud Village
properties.description: Eastern coast agricultural district. Banana and coconut production. Praslin and Mamiku Gardens nearby.

properties.name: Choiseul
properties.description: Arts and crafts district. Traditional Carib pottery. Balembouche Estate. Craft centre.

properties.name: Laborie
properties.description: Picturesque fishing village. Charming waterfront, authentic Creole culture, community tourism.

properties.name: Roseau Valley
properties.description: Major banana-growing valley. Traditionally the heart of St. Lucia's banana industry. Roseau River watershed.
properties._source_detail: Agricultural land use mapping + satellite imagery

properties.name: Central Forest Reserve
properties.description: Tropical rainforest. Edmund Forest Reserve, Quilesse Forest Reserve. Hiking trails (Enbas Saut, Barre de l'Isle). St. Lucia parrot habitat.

properties.name: Mabouya Valley
properties.description: Major agricultural valley in eastern St. Lucia. Banana and cocoa cultivation.
properties._source_detail: Agricultural land use mapping + satellite imagery

properties.name: Babonneau
properties.description: Inland agricultural community north of Castries. Small farms, residential. Rain Forest Adventures zipline nearby.

properties.name: Praslin / Mamiku
properties.description: Mamiku Gardens historic estate. Praslin Bay protected area. Fregate Islands Nature Reserve.

properties.name: Anse Chastanet Resort Area
properties.description: Anse Chastanet and Jade Mountain resorts. Premier diving location. Coral reef marine area.

properties.name: Cul de Sac Agricultural
properties.description: Banana and root crop farming area in the Cul de Sac valley, south of the industrial zone.

properties.name: Troumassee Solar + BESS Site
properties.description: Proposed 10MW solar PV + battery energy storage system (BESS). Micoud district. Under development.

properties.name: La Tourney Solar Farm
properties.description: 3MW solar PV farm. LUCELEC grid-connected. Rate: US$0.105/kWh. Operational.

properties.name: Rodney Bay Lagoon
properties.description: Inner lagoon. Marina, water sports, kayaking. Surrounding hotels and restaurants.

properties.name: The Morne / Castries Residential
properties.description: Hillside residential area overlooking Castries harbour. Government buildings on ridgeline.

properties.name: Anse Cochon Beach
properties.description: Popular snorkelling and diving beach. Accessible mainly by boat or rough track. Ti Kaye Resort.

properties.name: Anse Mamin Heritage Site
properties.description: Historic 18th-century plantation ruins. Hiking trails through tropical forest. Part of Anse Chastanet estate.
